4 Thanks to yelp, and Judd L's terrific review, we raced to BNC today for lunch.  I used his review as my cheat sheet because it sounded pretty comprehensive and great way to start to me.  Sadly the A-s aren't on the lunch menu anymore, BUT, we were able to order them from the dinner menu... And seated at a big table, our order of M1 (which is N1 on the lunch menu now), N4, P1, plus hot & sour soup along with both a chicken curry dish and the chicken nugget soup were pretty much devoured...there were only 4 of us...  No noodle making demos during lunch though.   We enjoyed everything - the noodles were delicious, slurpy, chewy, fresh and wonderful.    The pork and chive dumplings were divine, but ours today didn't come with their slurry "party hat" (seen in review pictures) which I think elevates dumplings far beyond simple potsticker status...    Their hot and sour soup - an ongoing yelp chat quixotic quest to find the best in town  - is pretty damned remarkable and worth remembering.  Theirs has that black vinegar sting that I LOVE which sort of takes your breath away when you swallow.  The ingredients are fresh and bright... the perfect cure for anything that might ail you... and if that doesn't work, try P1 - I think someone called their Beef Noodle Soup a marriage of pho and ramen...the broth was spicey, not with heat but with complexity -- and those noodles!    What we liked the least were the americanized Chinese dishes - those I'll be sure and steer clear of - but one of our guests wasn't a fan of pork so we wanted to make sure he had a little something extra - we gave this dish a definite C-, while the others were stars in their own right, even on a hot day in July.     I'd go back for dumplings, the hot and sour soup and to try the sold out scallion pancake alone... but oh, the slurpy goodness of those noodles.   And I've yet to have the beveled noodles... can't wait!  This may prove to be my undoing - given that it's so much easier to get to during lunch than Chinatown...   And the puzzle pieces are bhttp://www.yelp.com/eginning to fit together -- if this is the chef from Caesar's Beijing Noodle #9, then that explains why BN9 has hired the chef from China Mama...    Location: fortunately mentioned in yelp previously (or I wouldn't have clued in), this is the old Long Life Vegetarian place, located next door to Filfila, my current favorite Egyptian restaurant - in a godforsaken strip mall on the south east corner of Flamingo and Sandhill... don't let that be a put off...this is worth the excursion.    Service:  not that great, but not unbearable - but could use a little more focus...    Enjoy folks...this is a great new addition to the east side!  Yay!
